extensionDescription.message: Adds MyJDownloader to your browser, a service that enables you to remote control your JDownloader.

Allow the extension to run in privacy / incognito mode. This is needed if you want to force the extension to open captchas in incognito mode.

ui_settings_captcha_privacy_mode.message: Open captchas in private / incognito tabs

ui_settings_captcha_privacy_mode_descrip.message: Opening captchas in privacy mode makes it harder to track your solution attempts. This can improve or worsen your experience.

ui_settings_clipboard_observer_descripti.message: Detects links in your clipboard. Select something, then copy it. If your selection contains a link, the dialog to add or save the selection will pop up.

ui_settings_cnl_via_myjd_description.message: Intercepts Click'n'Load requests and sends them through MyJDownloader.

ui_settings_enhance_captcha_dialog_descr.message: If active, the web interface is able to display interactive and easier to use captchas.

ui_settings_show_add_links_dialog_descri.message: If active, a dialog is shown, allowing you to change values before sending links. If disabled, the links are sent using the default values. The dialog can't be deactivated if "Ask everytime" is the preferred target.

ui_settings_simple_contextmenu_descripti.message: If you use the simple context menu, the best fitting context is used (page, link or selection) and you do not have to choose what to add when using the right click menu to add links.

ui_settings_webinterface_enhancer_descri.message: You can add features to the MyJDownloader web interface by using this extension.
